<subSubSection pageNumber="451" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="451">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="451">Note:</emphasis>
<normalizedToken originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="451">Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
62: 1102. 1975) indicated 1020.4 or 1020.5 (LINN) as the type of the basionym, presumably in error as both are associated with the name &quot;
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eclipta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="latifolia">Eclipta latifolia</taxonomicName>
&quot; rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Verbesina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="451">V. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Neither they, nor 1020.7 (LINN), the post-1753 Patrick Browne collection treated as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
by Kupicha (in Davis, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="451">Fl. Turkey</emphasis>
5: 46. 1975), are original material for the name. Grierson (in Dassanayake &amp; Fosberg, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="451">Revised Handb. Fl. Ceylon</emphasis>
1: 212. 1980) treated material in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BM-SL">
Herb. Plukenet (
<collectionCode>BM-SL</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
, but this would not have been seen by Linnaeus and is not original material either. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wijnands’">Wijnands'</normalizedToken>
1983 choice of the Plukenet illustration as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
is therefore accepted here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
